HEADWORD: Hote
<hw>Hote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>pres. &
imp.</pos> <conjf>Hatte</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>, <conjf>Hot</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, etc.; <pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hote</conjf>,
<conjf>Hoten</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <conjf>Hot</conjf>, etc. See
<er>Hight</er>, <er>Hete</er>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To command; to
enjoin.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To promise.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be called; to be named.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There as I was wont to <qex>hote</qex> Arcite,⟦br⟧
Now hight I Philostrate, not worth a mite.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

